   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="letter">
            <pb n="1" facs="Edgeworth_Princeton_1815-03_page01.jpg"/>
            <opener>
               <dateline>
                  <name type="place" ref="Id_where"/>Dublin
                  <name type="place" ref="Id_where"/>15 Baggot Street
                  <date when="1815-03-14">March 14<hi rend="superscript">th</hi>. 1815.</date>
               </dateline>
               <salute>
                  <persName>My dear <persName ref="./Personography.xml#MileX1">Madam</persName>.</persName>
               </salute>
            </opener>
            <p>You will be glad to hear that the long lost<lb/>
               box has at last arrived in safety - and<lb/>
               the lace, muslin, <choice>
                  <orig>sattin</orig>
                  <reg>satin</reg>
               </choice> and white gauze<lb/>
               gown are all equal to our most <choice>
                  <orig>san<lb/>
               =guine</orig>
                  <reg>sanguine</reg>
               </choice> expectations &amp; we thank you for<lb/>
               having taken so much trouble and for<lb/>
               <choice>
                  <orig>chusing</orig>
                  <reg>choosing</reg>
               </choice> so well for us.<lb/>
            </p>
            <p>
               I am afraid you will feel vexed<lb/>
               at seeing the veil in this parcel, but<lb/>
               as it is much <hi rend="underline">larger</hi> &amp; more expensive<lb/>
               than I wished &amp; as the open work in the<lb/>
               border does not suit my fancy &amp; moreover<lb/>
               I am told does not wash well I avail<lb/>
               myself of your permission to return it<lb/>
               -- I need not say I hope that it has never<lb/>
               been worn -- Instead of it I should like<lb/>
               to have a bobbinet veil a yard <del>square</del>
               <add>wide</add>
               <lb/>
               is quite large enough for me - rounded at<lb/>
            </p>
            <p>
               <pb n="2" facs="Edgeworth_Princeton_1815-03_page02.jpg"/>
               The corners &amp; a simple chain border some<lb/>
               thing like this <figure>
                  <figDesc>Hand drawing of circular fabric pattern</figDesc>
               </figure>
               <lb/>
               If i must take lace to make up the difference<lb/>
               of price I wish you would <choice>
                  <orig>chuse</orig>
                  <reg>choose</reg>
               </choice> broad<lb/>
               lace for the bottom of a gown or any other<lb/>
               lace you approve - for lace is no loss<lb/>
            </p>
            <p>
               Send the veil &amp; lace between the covers<lb/>
               of books as I send this parcel - directed<lb/>
               to <persName ref="./Personography.xml#FoxC1">C.J. Fox Esq.<hi rend="superscript">re</hi>
               </persName> (for Miss E) under an outside<lb/>
               cover to <persName ref="./Personography.xml#TaylW1">W. Taylor Esq.<hi rend="superscript">re</hi>
               </persName>
               <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Castle-Dublin_IE">Castle - Dublin</placeName>
               <lb/>
            </p>
            <p>
               If <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EyleX1">Mr. Eyles</persName>
               <choice>
                  <orig>chuses</orig>
                  <reg>chooses</reg>
               </choice> to give the difference<lb/>
               between the price of the two veils in<lb/>
               money I beg you will pay <persName ref="./Personography.xml#SorrX1">Miss Sorrels</persName>
               <lb/>
               bill for my stay, &amp; if any balance remains<lb/>
               give it to <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeC1">Sneyd</persName> or his <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeH3">wife</persName> who are now<lb/>
               in London &amp; who desired that we should<lb/>
               direct to them at <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#St-Pauls-Churchyard_ENK">St. Pauls Church yard.</placeName>
               <lb/>
            </p>
            <p>
               Pray <hi rend="underline">tell</hi> that I am not as<lb/>
               troublesome as I know that I really am<lb/>
            </p>
            <closer>
               Your obliged servant<lb/>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeM1">Maria Edgeworth</persName>
               <lb/>
            </closer>
            <postscript>
